I arrived in the village of Galaba to a friend. She and her family members sat and drank tea. Tea was with sugar. During the conversation she told me about their Affairs. During the conversation she spoke about her entrepreneurial activities which start. After the deportation from Russia she could not find work. Rented 2ha of land and planted feed for the cattle and for the second year planted onions potatoes tomatoes herbs cucumbers. The yield was high she sold their products in the market and get good profit. She says a year three times to harvest. She bought the car Labo and built a house. She has two girls and two sons. The eldest daughter went to College in Khujand. Family live well other children are working in the field she's sitting on the market and sells its products.

I met a woman. She spoke about her entrepreneurial activities. It in his garden grow planting tomatoes cucumbers bell peppers and sells them in the market. She wants to open a greenhouse and expand your business activities. She has 5 children - 2 sons and 3 daughters. When I met her she didn't drink tea.

The woman told about herself.Due to financial difficulties she and her husband migrated to Russia on earnings. There she worked as a clerk in a toy store. After working there for several years, accumulating the money they came to Tajikistan and decided to open a shop selling children's toys.After the execution of all documents in the end, she along with her husband opened the shop. All kinds of toys to lie on her shelves. And the prices is very affordable. Basically the store she sits and sells and the husband is engaged in other matters.

The woman told about herself.Married a bad husband was a bum didn't want to work. With the help of parents she rented a place in the local market and was selling different spices. The husband has migrated to Russia to work but any money he sends. She has two children. Now she thinks she should go to work in Russia.

I met up with a friend she's married and has two children. By profession a dressmaker. When I went to her home they all family members sitting and drinking tea. The tea was lemon and sugar. She works as a dressmaker and at the expense of their income bought a sewing machine Hawrelak and one machine is equipped with a computer. Dad WWII veteran, she leased the land and began to farm. She works as a tailor and engaged in farming. Due to their earnings, she bought a house. Live well.

The woman told her friend.Is engaged in the manufacture and sale of invitation cards for various events. Husband died from the disease. Children all family i.e. they have their own family. Tired of sitting at home doing nothing. Together with my daughter decided to pursue the case. Recently rented a premises and opened a store not so very much but what to do?! Especially in summer and autumn can be a lot of orders.

Met a woman and she told me about his activities. She buys bones from the market separates unground and sells in the market and the remainder collects in a bag and each bag sells for 15-20 somoni. Due to their earnings, she bought a special equipment for separation of bone and repaired his house. She is married and has two sons and wants to do children to University. Has expanded its business and improved the family fortune. When I went to her room she sat and drank tea without sugar or lemon.

I met a woman at the house of his relative. She told of one man who was divorced. We sat at the table and drank tea without sugar and no lemon. The man is divorced and has 3 children - two girls and one son. He borrowed money and started his own business. He bought a small-horned and cattle. In the first year it nothing happened. Within 2-3 years, his business became better, the number of cattle increased and he started to sell milk and yogurt. He also rented a 2ha land grew food for their cattle. The income was good. He bought a tractor and a porter and built a house. Now live well and your business also expanded. In the future, to open a farm.

Talk about the entrepreneurial activities of its mugami husband for many years engaged in private enterprise. Early in his career, he took a loan from the Bank in the amount of 8000<U+0441><U+043E><U+043C><U+043E><U+043D><U+0438> started a business selling agricultural products. He bought goods from local farmers and sold on the market. Due to his business he received a good profit and even the first years, he paid the loan. However, my husband and I have decided to produce and sell their products. And so in order to take the land we have addressed a statement to Chucumata area and they gave us 2ha of land. We started to produce products. The first year we went out together on the ground to work the land planted to rice 50sotok 50sotok tomato 30 acres cucumbers 20 acres of pepper and 50sotok gourds and got very good profit. So we're all a family for 4-5 engaged in agricultural business are improving your life.

Tell us about your business activities.I have for many years engaged in business. I started my activity in the sales of school and children's garments. I have continued my business for 4-5 years but due to his punktualnost went bankrupt in the 3-4 years I was unemployment and sitting at home. Nose every day life is getting heavier and I decided to start a business. This time I started a business selling agricultural product. One part of the product I grow on my farm, I take another part from the neighbors. How to sell a product the money will give them and I still have a little money now at the expense of profit of your business live.

Talk about former Acadamy used to live in Shahrinav district. With us in the neighborhood lived a poor but very humble and kind neighbor. Her husband worked as a policeman but in 1992-1993, he was killed. They lived in poor and even due to lack of money her children could not go to school. All the inhabitants of our village helped them possible, but at that time life was very difficult. We are neighbors, together with the Chairman of the village Council collected the money and her son who was in the 10-11 class go to Russia on earnings. We sent it to one of our friend who has long worked in Russia to help him get a job. He tripled it to work, began to send money to my mother and my mother lived here at the expense of the money which the son sends. After 3-4 years the son returned from migration and opened a shop in the market district Shahrinav and opened their business. Gradually life became better. Now in the next 4-5 years the whole family has been in business and get good profit. He has already expanded its activities and has its own house and a car.

Tell about the business activities of his uncle.Uncle for many years worked on migration each year, came to visit his family and after 10 to 20 days back have migrated. Last time he went to Russia with him was not allowed to enter the country since he was deported last time. He returned to Tajikistan and did not know what to do. His friends advised him to open a grocery store because in this village there is a grocery store. He agreed and opened a store near his home. In order to start your business he took a long-term loan from the Bank in the amount of 15000<U+0441><U+043E><U+043C><U+043E><U+043D><U+0438> and began operations. After 5-6 months instead of a profit he went bankrupt because so many were in debt and could not return the money. The term Bank loan has expired and he could not pay back the loan. Then he took out a loan from another Bank in the amount of 15,000 TJS gave the first Bank and now does not know how to find the money to pay the second Bank.

Talk about the entrepreneurial activities of its mugami husband for many years, no where to work and only had his little farm. He was engaged in farming. Over time, the children grew up some of them went to University someone else in school. Life was harder and we didn't know how to solve all these problems. With one hand the money to the sons who are studying in University on the other side of the family expenses. My husband and I decided to start the business of their cattle and turned. Husband sold one cattle and bought the place 5 small (sheep). Within 1-2 months, he fed them, and sold expensive. After get good profit, we opened a butcher shop. My husband bought livestock from local farmers, some of them left on his farm as part of the slaughtered for meat and sold in the store. And so we got a good income and have opened a new grocery store near his home. Now live well and get good profit.

Talk about the other Man engaged in the sale of motor vehicles: supply from Lithuania cars to Tajikistan. At first the business was very profitable because there were no big prices for customs clearance. With working capital 30 000$/35000$ can was at least 2500/3000 earn clean. However, the last 2 years prices for cars sharply slept. Reasons:1. Big clearance on the cheap car G. V. 1996 - 1997 to 2000. Price of customs clearance is raised by 40% 2. Deport citizens of RF in RT: lack of cash.3. Tough and large competition, too many sellers <U+0430><U+0432><U+0442><U+043E>4. House Dushevina: one sold for half the price and this gave hope a buyer to have a car for half the price. Started to bring down prices.In the end, at the moment all cars are either sold into debt for no profit or are not bringing money with a/c

The story of a family business (the hardware store)My husband is no where to work and I was forced to do business. My father sold household goods in Kulyab and I went to him for the goods and sold them in Muminabad sometimes I change the fruit. Gradually I expanded my business and opened his own shop. At the moment business is going well.

In order to start their business I took out a loan in the amount of 600<U+0441><U+043E><U+043C><U+043E><U+043D><U+0438> and opened a grocery store near his home. I bought products from wholesalers and sold in his shop. I provided his family through their income. After one year I increased the amount of goods and expanded her business. The moment I paid off the loan and improve family conditions.

Abdurahmonova Nargis 38-years living in Shahritus district. For 4 years has been in the food business. She is married and has 6 children - 4 daughters and two sons. Nargis has secondary incomplete education and took a 6 month course on entrepreneurship. Before her husband had his own business activities but after he got sick he had to close his business. Nargis had to rent a shop in Tojikmatlubot" and start your business activities. "If "Tojikmatlubot" different looking reason would not take the money I have bought a car and a house," she says.

Abdushukurova Fatima was born in 1995 and married has a secondary education Living in Shahritus district at the village of Kh. Kholmatov the village of Karl Marx. She went to the sewing workshop "Sukhrob" and started a sewing business at home. Worked for two years and my sister was attracted to the work. During the two years prior to the marriage, she could afford to buy all the necessary dowry (jewelry bedroom sets, etc.). Also helped their parents.The story told by her mom 42 years has a secondary education and five children. Her husband of 48 years employed.

Woman her name is Maysara 50 years and has 4 children. Together with her husband a few years ago started a business selling men's shoes. to start a business helped relatives then to promote your business took out a loan in the Bank. Opened a small Shoe store. Competitors were few. income was satisfactory. Did repairs at home bought new home appliances, everything is new. At the moment she has several shops ie it has expanded its business and now she sells not only shoes but also men's clothes and this helped her husband sons and daughter-in-law. Grandchildren go to prestigious kindergartens. She is doing well.

column92: unemployed and not looking for work

Woman her name is Munira 33 years and has two children. Married. Recently started my business after the money. Decided to open a children's clothing store. Was in this business for long. And she had to close the shop. things she distributed in different stores. Now sitting and thinking how to repay the debt.

Woman's Uminia and she's 58-years.A few years ago a grocery store near his home. Due to the good income made repairs at home built a new house for his son. She has regular customers because there is no competition. The only grocery store in the village. All the inhabitants of the village come to her shop. Gradually freshened up his shop expanded area of the store and it was spacious. A kind of goods became more attractive more customers. Business to her liking.

Woman her name is Saodat 45-years is married and has three children. The family also has father-in-law and mother-in-law. My husband works as a security guard. Money in the family was not enough and Saodat have decided to do something. Every day she early in the morning left the house to buy milk. This she did for a living. in addition, she has always had cow - males she babysits and when they reach the required weight she along with her husband sells them. This is another type of business. Due to this, she has given two daughters in marriage. Now her work has been her mother-in-law who stays at home helping her and her son, who grew up in. And she simultaneously works in the dining room cook.

I am 47 years old widow, have 3 children education higher sell food. Start your business for personal money. Due to his business has given two daughters married she married. Son lives with me. Happy life wealth on average.

I am 40 years old married have 4 children: 3 daughters and a son. The education received is average. Start your business without any initial Deposit. In season they sell about 55-60 kg of strawberries, the proceeds of which Supplement our family budget and provides an additional source for daily expenses.

Female 35 years married with one child education secondary, specialty seamstress-Croisic. Start your own business with the purchase of sewing machines for the debt obtained from relatives. After a year at the expense of income acquired a machine for embroidery. For more than 10 years of living at the expense of his business. Currently owns a small sewing shop where employs 5 people and teaches them to sew.

A young woman 27 years old married have 1 child incomplete secondary education. More than 7 years of experience in sewing curtains. After 3 years, helped two of his relatives to learn this business and at present all of them due to this business to support their families.

column105: The woman is about 45 to 47 years, married, has 3 children, about education, don't know. Rented the dining room and for 5 years was prepared and sold food. A woman approximately 35 years married housewife the life was very hard. After receiving a grant from an international organization bought a cash cow and due to the sale of milk has established its financial condition. After 2 years the cow gave birth to calf is a little raised and sold the calf she bought another cow. A year later another calf. So in about 4 years the woman's life began to improve when previously it sold only milk but now she is engaged in the production and selling of butter, cream and kurut Chucky for the past 5 years, exports its products to sell in the city.

column92: unemployed and not looking for work
column105: Female approx 55-57 years married has 1 child, secondary education. Start your business on the money of a son who was in labor migration. Bought 2 cows, raised them and then sold. Thus increase constantly the number of cattle and conducts his farm. Says that due to its income leads the social work and today it does not need remittances.

Male 43-45 years has 4 children of secondary education by profession a farmer marital status below average. At first he lived by decanta. Then started his own business with the help of the international program and became the owner of the machine for packing of Shilajit and other useful plants. For 1 year at the expense of profits gained in and fry turned a small pond near the house in the fish pond. Within 2 years the profits from the sale of fish and medicinal plants was able to purchase 1 cow. In subsequent years, received income from three sources: the mummy and medicinal plants, fish and cows. Thus married their children and purchased a car.

I am 65 years old have seven grandchildren doing decanta secondary education. For 10 years of beekeeping. For the initial capital took out a loan in German Agroaction and used the proceeds to purchase 5 boxes with bees. After a year at the expense of income from those bees acquired another 10 boxes. Life through the sale of honey began to improve. Are currently a member of the Association of beekeeping.

After graduating University I worked in a plant for the repair of electronic equipment. Work was good but the wages was low. My parents decided to open their own business. For this I took out a loan from the Bank rented premises in the city and opened his own company for the repair of electronic equipment. In the beginning the work was difficult because I was working alone and the work was hard. Then I invited my colleagues and together we started work. We are now working four and work has become easier In the future want to expand my work and get more profit.

Talk about your sister.My sister has two children but after her husband died she was difficult to feed their children and earn. She didn't know what to do. I recommended her to Sambuca cake she baked and sold the market. She did that for several years she sold the pies and now she's got a stall for the preparation sambusa and cake. In this way she has improved the family fortune.

After graduation my parents wanted me to go to medical school but I refused and decided to become a dressmaker. They agreed and I enrolled in vocational school in our city and finished. I together with my friends have opened a sewing shop in my house. We not only sew national women's dresses but also make men's and European fashion. We are very well established work and every day customers come more and more. We are now collecting your income and in future I want to open a large sewing shop with modern equipment. I hope that our dream to be fulfilled.

I have decided to open a Bridal salon. Last year my husband talked about it and I'm from another salon rented wedding dress and brought to the village. I announced that residents can rent I have a wedding to pay. In the beginning the work went well and I brought other new dresses at a high price. But maybe because of lack of money or high prices of rent clients to me never came back. And the rent for the elephant which took them dress every day has accumulated and I had to return the dress and pay the rent which had accumulated.

The story about your friend.My friend, entrepreneur and opened a plant for the production of alcoholic drink. But he had problems. I have experience and knowledge in this area and he recommended that to raise the quality of beverages delivered the product to the shops sometimes to take in debt and to advertise on the market. After he bought the truck "Forland" and began to deliver the finished products to other entrepreneurs in the market and shopping. At the moment he delivers food in areas of Vakhsh and Bokhtar in other subject areas of Kurgan-Tyube.

Talk about my start a business selling fruit and vegetables this was a seasonal business.And in other seasons sold food. After a few years began to sell clothing. But when I went for the items I closed the shop. For 2-3 days prior to my arrival, the store was close and who was trading. Due to the absence of the assistant - permanent seller I was forced to close such business.

The story of the entrepreneurial activities of our family.Earlier in our village except the grocery store was no longer the other stores and pharmacies. We and the other inhabitants of this village to buy drugs, went to the city center. Was very difficult to ride because our village is located very far from the city centre. At that time I and my brothers went to medical College. The parents decided to open a pharmacy in our village. In order to open a pharmacy we took out a loan from the Bank, rented reset the building which was in our village, repaired and opened a pharmacy. In this way we could solve the problems of the residents of our village to deliver the medicine and in future I want to open a clothing store.

Widow 49 years, has 2 daughters education. Daughters age of about 18 then 29 years old. 5 years ago I found a small table near his house and started to sell every little thing (seeds kurut chewing gum). With the profits and the help of relatives acquired a trade booth and increased the range of goods for sale. OVER the last 3-4 years have received a considerable profit of priorel 2 acres of land opened his own shop. This store sells food and household stuff. Now vreya works in the store along with son-in-law. From the profits were able to buy a car Opel Astra and repair your home.

Muhidinov said 28 years have 4 children education married. The husband also secondary education is not currently working. Children aged 3 to 10 years. The difficult situation forced her to do business. Due to the lack of higher education she learned from friends baking sweet goods (muffins chak-chak cakes) and started to sell their baked goods at the market Rayna Bokhtar. The market had its outlets. In 2 years he acquired a circle of regular customers. She currently bakes cakes fatir and Kalam. Clients take a day from 100 to 200 cakes and faterov a day. Husband helps her with her work. Due to its profit bought a washing machine and a large oven. In this business 2-3 years and provides the family.

Mirzarahimova Kurbongul 58 years, has 8 children education secondary. Within 10 years leases the land in dehkan farms "Bobo Maqsood" where together with her husband and children grows tomatoes watermelon beans cotton potatoes. From the profits were able to give higher education to his 5 daughters one of the sons received higher technical education. Currently, one of the sons is employment migration. Once Kurbongul participated at the training organized by the public organization "Zarnisor" where he gained very useful knowledge. Scored his share of 1 hectare and 56 acres for himself. In 2015 received 15 quintals of cotton from 1 hectare of land thus having a profit of 10,000 somoni. 50 acres of land planted with wheat received 2 tons of harvest provided its annual reserve. Due to its net profit was married off 5 daughters. Certificate of land received free of charge. In the future, intends to find more funds to increase your business. Want to buy large greenhouses and expand your business.

The girl of 18 years has a secondary education living with their parents. Their family of 5 people has 2 brothers. Since 7th grade I learned this from my aunt's sewing cherosov and embroidery for pillowcases that her neighbor sells on the market. Per month net income is up to 200 somoni. At the expense of their profits helps the family. Is engaged in this business for 4 years. One of her brothers is in migration and sends money for the family.

Course organized by public organizations have improved their knowledge and in their home has created 10 jobs. Within 3 months she conducted training among 10 girls 50 somoni each month. Is currently working with 10 employees accept orders for tailoring of kurpacha tablecloths pillows of TUBITAK, etc. last year were able to purchase for 300 dollar sewing machine "Yamata" and for $ 200 serger. Fully provide for the family the husband is currently in labor migration. In the future she wants to open her sewing shop and buy new equipment to expand their business.

My interviewee was a 48-year-old woman who told the story of the business to his daughter-in-law who started her own business of 25 years with the sale of carpets. In this business it was very supportive of Lena's family. Over 6 years of activity she was able to expand his shop. Currently, income from your business, it is taking land in the center of the village began construction of the store "hardware store". Very good that she always plans his work and takes into account your income correctly. Correctly distributes your finances do not spend money in vain. Wants to continue to educate their sons in the universities of Russia.

Its main business is the provision of teachers of common schools. Signing the contract with the school district on behalf of the sewing shops of the city of Kanibadam provides clothing to school. According to her more than 10 years she has been selling women's clothing, plans in 2017 to open a branch shop in Asht district.

My interviewee was a 50-year-old woman has 4 children and 6 grandchildren. In 2014 she completed courses "Sewing adras and Atlas" in Khujand city and received a certificate. Started its activities by organizing 2 points on sewing adras in the center of the support women in their area. At first, her students were her 2 daughters and daughter-in-law. For eighteen years she taught sewing adras a dozen girls. At present, in the clothing shop which is located in the women's support Center they are engaged in sewing of adras and Atlas national and European dresses bags scarves shawls. Four glasses are 6 people planning to increase the number of points to ten and to increase the number of employees.

In 2010, the village was organized the Project "Social preparation of families of labour migrants" on the basis of which the groups were created. She became the leader of one group called "Zebo-2" which combined with 8 women. Joint work floor well on the proceeds it contained the family improved their financial position. Women participated in courses and trainings to increase their skills. Getting a loan in the Eamon expanded his business. Living in Jamoat Kulkand.

In the store except the office of also sell perfumes gifts Newspapers and magazines. Their store is always a lot of customers because in their area there is no such store.
